&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &#39;times new roman&#39;, times, serif; font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;Interested in joining a growing company where you will work with talented colleagues, enhance a supportive and energetic culture, and be part of the climate solution? At Energy Solutions, we focus on the big impacts. And we believe that market-based programs can be a powerful force to deliver large-scale energy, carbon, and water-use savings. Since 1995, we’ve harnessed that power to offer proven, performance-based solutions for our utility, government, and institutional customers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &#39;times new roman&#39;, times, serif; font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;Energy Solutions is seeking a full-time &lt;strong&gt;Solar Associate, REC Contracts&lt;/strong&gt;, to join our Distributed Energy Resources (DER) Team. The Solar Associate will execute and own a defined segment of program operations, supporting contract-related workflows that impact multiple applications simultaneously. This role processes large spreadsheet-based batches of applications, performing project extensions, project removals, and Schedule B updates on a rotating basis while ensuring data integrity, compliance, and adherence to established SOPs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &#39;times new roman&#39;, times, serif; font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;You will operate within a highly collaborative, sequential workflow—receiving completed applications from preceding steps, executing your tasks with precision, and passing the torch to the next team member for review. While external communication is minimal, you will occasionally participate in client-facing meetings and reporting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &#39;times new roman&#39;, times, serif; font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &#39;times new roman&#39;, times, serif; font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The person filling this role will be required to work in a hybrid work environment reporting to one of our offices in Oakland, CA;&amp;nbsp; Portland, OR; Chicago, IL and expected to be in the office a minimum of once a week.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &#39;times new roman&#39;, times, serif; font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
